$ %WindowsSdkDir%

The → Windows/development/Visual-Studio/environment-variables[Visual Studio environment variable] `%WindowsSdkDir%` points to the → Windows/development/Kits[Windows kits] directory.
-
A possible value of this variable might be `C:\Program Files (x86)\Windows Kits\10`.

Apparently, the value of `%UniversalCRTSdkDir%` also points to the same directory.

Some subirectories include
  • App Certification Kit
  • → Windows/dirs/Program-Files-x86/Windows-Kits/n/bin[bin]
  • Catalogs
  • → Windows/dirs/Program-Files-x86/Windows-Kits/n/Debuggers[Debuggers]
  • DesignTime
  • Extension SDKs
  • → Windows/dirs/Program-Files-x86/Windows-Kits/n/Include[Include]
  • → Windows/dirs/Program-Files-x86/Windows-Kits/n/Lib[Lib]
  • Licenses
  • Platforms
  • Redist
  • References
  • Remote
  • Shortcuts
  • → Windows/dirs/Program-Files-x86/Windows-Kits/n/Source[Source]
  • → Windows/dirs/Program-Files-x86/Windows-Kits/n/Tools[Tools] (?)
  • Testing
  • UnionMetadata
  • → Windows/dirs/Program-Files-x86/Windows-Kits/n/Vsix[Vsix] (?)
  • → Windows/dirs/Program-Files-x86/Windows-Kits/n/Windows-Performance-Toolkit[Windows Performance Toolkit]

sa:
  The value of `InstallationFolder` under `→ Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/Software/Microsoft/Microsoft-SDKs/Windows/_version`.

